There are three simulated reads data generated using GemSim (KE McElroy, F Luciani, T Thomas. Gemsim: General, Error-Model Based Simulator of Next-Generation Sequencing Data. BMC Genomics 2012, 13:74), with coverage 50x, 60x, 100x, read lengths 100-bp.

Users can download them and run PERGA using these data sets.

Assembly command:
$ ./perga all -k 25 -p 2 -f gemSim_1.16m_50x.fastq -d out_result -o gemSim_50x

Then the the results will be output to 'out_result', 'gemSim_50x_contigs.fa' and 'gemSim_50x_scaffolds.fa' are the final results.

Thank you for enjoying it!
